# Backend Filter & Sort DTO Pattern

## Sort Constants File (`constants/<entity>-sort.constants.ts`)

Every filterable module needs a sort constants file with this exact structure:

```typescript
export const ENTITY_SORT_BY_FIELDS = ['field1', 'field2', 'date'] as const;
export type EntitySortByField = (typeof ENTITY_SORT_BY_FIELDS)[number];

export const ENTITY_SORT_COLUMN_MAP: Record<EntitySortByField, string> = {
  field1: 'entity.field1',   // TypeORM QB alias.column
  field2: 'entity.field2',
  date: 'entity.date',
};

export const ENTITY_SORT_ORDER_VALUES = ['ASC', 'DESC'] as const;
export type EntitySortOrder = (typeof ENTITY_SORT_ORDER_VALUES)[number];
```

## Filter DTO (`dto/<entity>-filter.dto.ts`)

```typescript
export class EntityFilterDto {
  // --- Domain filters (enum, boolean, UUID, string) ---
  @IsEnum(SomeEnum)
  @IsOptional()
  type?: SomeEnum;

  @IsString()
  @IsOptional()
  search?: string;

  @IsUUID('4')
  @IsOptional()
  relatedId?: string;

  @IsBoolean()
  @IsOptional()
  @Type(() => Boolean)
  flag?: boolean;

  // --- Pagination (always same) ---
  @IsInt() @Min(1) @IsOptional() @Type(() => Number)
  page?: number = 1;

  @IsInt() @Min(1) @Max(100) @IsOptional() @Type(() => Number)
  limit?: number = 50;

  // --- Sort (reference constants) ---
  @IsIn(ENTITY_SORT_BY_FIELDS) @IsOptional()
  sortBy?: (typeof ENTITY_SORT_BY_FIELDS)[number];

  @IsIn(ENTITY_SORT_ORDER_VALUES) @IsOptional() @Type(() => String)
  sortOrder?: (typeof ENTITY_SORT_ORDER_VALUES)[number];
}
```

## Service `resolveSortColumn()` Method

```typescript
private resolveSortColumn(sortBy?: string): string {
  if (sortBy && sortBy in ENTITY_SORT_COLUMN_MAP) {
    return ENTITY_SORT_COLUMN_MAP[sortBy as EntitySortByField];
  }
  return 'entity.defaultField'; // fallback
}
```

## Key Rules

- **Pagination defaults**: `page=1`, `limit=50`, max `100`
- **Sort whitelist**: reject invalid `sortBy` via `@IsIn()` — never trust raw user input in `ORDER BY`
- **`@Type(() => Number)`**: required on all numeric query params (query string is always string)
- **Array params**: use `@Transform` to coerce scalar to array (see `positionIds` in PersonFilterDto)
- **Spec file**: always test valid/invalid `sortBy` and `sortOrder` values
